Author: Gateway#3763
Content:
[dscrdpioneers] <Mylo(KomodoPioneers)> have a look at html5 games on github.  plenty there.  html5 games are easy to work with - html5 game engines: https://github.com/collections/javascript-game-engines  phaser is good.

you use any of those game engines in a google search and " tutorial" or " sample" and there'll be plenty of stuff that has been started that can be modded no probs.

then if you want to go a bit more hardcore, there's unity3d.com and unreal engine.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrdpioneers] <Mylo(KomodoPioneers)> so pick your genre, top down shooter, 1st person, 3rd person, platformer, infinite runner etc.  there's also a marketplace on unity3d for out-of-the-box simple games.  depending what the goal is - have a look at the unity assetstore https://assetstore.unity.com/categories/templates

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrdpioneers] <Mylo(KomodoPioneers)> e.g. https://assetstore.unity.com/packages/templates/packs/bubble-break-95719
